PRION DISEASE UPDATE 2011 (03)
******************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

[With the continuing decline of the number of cases in the human
population of variant Creutzfeldt-Jakob disease -- abbreviated
previously as vCJD or CJD (new var.) in ProMED-mail -- it has been
decided to broaden the scope of the occasional ProMED-mail updates to
include other prion-related diseases. In addition to vCJD, data on
other forms of CJD: sporadic, iatrogenic, familial, and GSS
(Gerstmann-Straussler-Scheinker disease) are included also since they
may have some relevance to the incidence and etiology of vCJD. -
Mod.CP]

In this update:
[1] UK: National CJD Surveillance Unit - monthly statistics as of Wed
9 Mar 2011 - new vCJD case
[2] France: Institut de Veille Sanitaire - monthly statistics as of
Tue 1 Mar 2011 - no new vCJD cases
[3] USA: National Prion Disease Pathology Surveillance Center -
cumulative case numbers for 2010 up to 1 Nov 2010 - no vCJD cases
[4] UK: HPA biannual update
[5] Prions in peripheral tissue
[6] Taiwan: suspected case statement

******
[1] UK: National CJD Surveillance Unit - monthly statistics as of Wed
9 Mar 2011 - new vCJD case
Date: Wed 9 Mar 2011
Source: UK National CJD Surveillance Unit, monthly statistics
[edited]
<http://www.cjd.ed.ac.uk/figures.htm>


The number of deaths due to definite or probable vCJD as of 9 Mar
2011 has increased by one to 171. A total of 4 definite/probable
patients remain alive so the total number of definite or probable vCJD
cases becomes 175.

Although a new case of vCJD has been identified in 2011, the overall
picture is still consistent with the view that the vCJD outbreak in
the UK is in decline, albeit now with a pronounced tail. The 1st cases
were observed in 1995, and the peak number of deaths was 28 in the
year 2000, followed by 20 in 2001, 17 in 2002, 18 in 2003, 9 in 2004,
5 in 2005, 5 in 2006, 5 in 2007, 1 in 2008, 3 in 2009, 3 in 2010, and
1 so far in 2011.

Totals for all types of CJD cases in the UK in the year 2011
------------------------------------------------------------
During 2011 so far [as of 9 Mar 2011], there have been 27 referrals,
11 fatal cases of sporadic CJD, 1 case of GSS, 1 case of familial CJD,
1 case of vCJD, and none of iatrogenic CJD.

Since records began in 1990 there have been 2758 referrals, 1216
fatal cases of sporadic CJD, 171 cases of vCJD, 65 cases of iatrogenic
CJD, 83 cases of familial CJD, and 44 of GSS.

--
